"title": "5674: daughters",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5674: daughters",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The female offspring of parents. Daughters lived in their father's house, under his protection, until marriage. Usually they became his heirs only if he had no sons to inherit his estate. Normally they shared in the inheritance of their husbands.</p>\n<h2>Protection of daughters</h2>\n<h3>Fathers were responsible for protecting their daughters</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen31:50\">GEN 31:50</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen19:12-Gen19:13\">GEN 19:12–19:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen19:15-Gen19:17\">GEN 19:15–19:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num30:3-Num30:5\">NUM 30:3–30:5</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of fathers who failed to protect their daughters</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen19:8\">GEN 19:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg19:24\">JDG 19:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam13:6-2Sam13:14\">2SA 13:6–13:14</a></p>\n<h2>Marriage of daughters</h2>\n<h3>Fathers were responsible for arranging marriages for their daughters</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen34:8-Gen34:9\">GEN 34:8–34:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen29:26\">GEN 29:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh15:16-Josh15:17\">JOS 15:16–15:17</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg1:12-Judg1:13\">JDG 1:12–1:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg12:9\">JDG 12:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg21:1\">JDG 21:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam18:17-1Sam18:21\">1SA 18:17–18:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:44\">1SA 25:44</a></p>\n<h3>Fathers received a bride-price from their daughters' husbands</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam18:25\">1SA 18:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen29:16-Gen29:27\">GEN 29:16–29:27</a></p>\n<h3>Fathers gave a dowry to their daughters</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs9:16\">1KI 9:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh15:17-Josh15:19\">JOS 15:17–15:19</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg1:13-Judg1:15\">JDG 1:13–1:15</a></p>\n<h3>Sometimes the marriage of a daughter was the basis of a political alliance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs3:1\">1KI 3:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan11:6\">DAN 11:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan11:17\">DAN 11:17</a></p>\n<h3>In cases of dispute, parents were expected to prove their daughter's virginity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:13-Deut22:21\">DEU 22:13–22:21</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Inheritance of daughters</h2>\n<h3>If a man had no sons, the inheritance went to his daughters</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num27:1-Num27:11\">NUM 27:1–27:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh17:3-Josh17:6\">JOS 17:3–17:6</a></p>\n<h3>Daughters who inherited their father's property were obliged to marry within his clan</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num36:1-Num36:12\">NUM 36:1–36:12</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Job allocated his daughters an inheritance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job42:13-Job42:15\">JOB 42:13–42:15</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Priests' daughters</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev10:14\">LEV 10:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev21:1-Lev21:2\">LEV 21:1–21:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev21:9\">LEV 21:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev22:12-Lev22:13\">LEV 22:12–22:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:11\">NUM 18:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:19\">NUM 18:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek44:25\">EZK 44:25</a></p>\n<h2>Slavery of daughters</h2>\n<h3>In dire circumstances fathers sometimes sold their daughters into slavery</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh5:5\">NEH 5:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:7\">EXO 21:7</a></p>\n<h3>A slave girl married to a son was to be accorded the rights of a daughter</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:9\">EXO 21:9</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Immorality of daughters</h2>\n<h3>Prostitution of daughters forbidden</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:29\">LEV 19:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev21:9\">LEV 21:9</a></p>\n<h3>Incest of Lot's daughters</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen19:30-Gen19:38\">GEN 19:30–19:38</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Daughters-in-law</h2>\n<h3>Sexual relations with daughters-in-law forbidden</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev18:15\">LEV 18:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:12\">LEV 20:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek22:11\">EZK 22:11</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of daughters-in-law</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth4:14-Ruth4:15\">RUT 4:14–4:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen38:6-Gen38:26\">GEN 38:6–38:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth1:3-Ruth1:17\">RUT 1:3–1:17</a></p>\n<h2>Daughters in a spiritual role</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts21:9\">ACT 21:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:28\">JOL 2:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:17\">ACT 2:17</a></p>\n<h2>An adopted daughter</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth2:7\">EST 2:7</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Daughter in a non-literal sense</h2>\n<h3>Of an area, town or country or its population</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:5\">MAT 21:5</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:15\">JHN 12:15</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs19:21\">2KI 19:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps137:8\">PSA 137:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa10:30\">ISA 10:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa23:12\">ISA 23:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa52:2\">ISA 52:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer6:23\">JER 6:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer48:18\">JER 48:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer51:33\">JER 51:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam1:15\">LAM 1:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam2:10\">LAM 2:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic4:8\">MIC 4:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph3:14\">ZEP 3:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech2:7\">ZEC 2:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech9:9\">ZEC 9:9</a></p>\n<h3>Of the female inhabitants of an area, town or country</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:27-Luke23:29\">LUK 23:27–23:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:3\">GEN 24:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:13\">GEN 24:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam1:24\">2SA 1:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song3:5\">SNG 3:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song5:8\">SNG 5:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa32:9-Isa32:11\">ISA 32:9–32:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek13:17\">EZK 13:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek32:18\">EZK 32:18</a></p>\n<h3>Of the female descendants</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:16\">LUK 13:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:5-1Pet3:6\">1PE 3:5–3:6</a></p>\n<h3>As an honorific term</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:22\">MAT 9:22</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:34\">MRK 5:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:48\">LUK 8:48</a></p>\n<h2>Daughters in a theological sense</h2>\n<h3>God's people are his sons and daughters</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:18\">2CO 6:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer14:17\">JER 14:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:21-Jer31:22\">JER 31:21–31:22</a></p>\n<h3>Family relationships must be subservient to one's relationship with God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:37\">MAT 10:37</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:35\">MAT 10:35</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:53\">LUK 12:53</a></p>",
